Expanding, we get
\[b^2 + x^2 = a^2 - 2ax + x^2 + b^2 - 2by + y^2.\]Hence,
\[a^2 + y^2 = 2ax + 2by.\]Note that
\[2by > 2y^2 \ge y^2,\]so $2by - y^2 \ge 0.$  Since $2by - y^2 = a^2 - 2ax,$ $a^2 - 2ax \ge 0,$ or
